The paper focuses on joint modeling of social networks and mobile trajectories, which falls under the category of social networks and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel neural network model, which involves training and optimization, making it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the correlation between social connections and trajectory behaviors, which is a topic of interest in cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). The paper also employs RNN and GRU models, which are commonly used in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) for sequence modeling and data management, respectively.
